<ptxt>INSPECT FRONT SEAT FRAME WITH ADJUSTER LH</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="B081621E19" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check operation of the seat frame (slide motor).</ptxt>
<s3>
<ptxt>Check if the seat frame moves smoothly when the battery is connected to the slide motor connector terminals.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Measurement Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Operational Direction</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Battery positive (+) → U1-1</ptxt>
<ptxt>Battery negative (-) → U1-2</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Forward</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Battery positive (+) → U1-2</ptxt>
<ptxt>Battery negative (-) → U1-1</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Backward</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the result is not as specified, replace the seat frame with adjuster.</ptxt>
</s3>
